narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a phenomenal class, and I definitely recommend it to anyone looking for a fun/interesting seminar. MP is an awesome professor and keeps the class fun (he brought in food for one of the discussions about Mexican food). You should definitely take this (or similar) class if it is offered.

This course provides great historical background for many contemporary issues revolving around Mexicans and Mexican-Americans. Throughout this course students will be exposed to multiple facets of these cultures and defining moments throughout the history of these people in the United States.
I would recommend this course. It was my favorite of the semester and I looked forward to class each week. I learned so much and I always felt engaged w the material.
Yes I would recommend this class. It was enjoyable in the sense that the material was interesting/ engaging and had a reasonable amount of work.

You learn a lot about all different aspects of immigrant life for Mexican Americans. You learn a lot of important things too about the history of this demographic. The professor is great and discussions were very interesting.
